The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 April is 41,516 (4,805.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 April, there were 109 new confirmed cases (12.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 March, there were 201 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 46% (92 fewer cases).
